race.comment: LORD ARCADIA (8) was left with too much to do on resumption at Bunbury when getting a mile back over 1400m. Now straight up to the mile, Chris Parnham hops on board and the gelding draws much better this time around. Can shed his maiden tag. SANABEAU (5) is better than we saw last time out when dropping back to the 1400m journey. Her effort over this track and trip two back was sound and this looks a more suitable race than what she tackled most recently. Has the speed to roll across and can put her best foot forward. LET'S SEA (4) dropped right back in trip last start and turned in a better effort than we saw two back. The claim of Tsang means he's still right down in the weights and this trip looks his best. Can be thereabouts. MIFF MUFFERED MOOF (3) won well last start and creates some interest coming back in trip. THE RUSH (2) is next best out to the mile now.
